**Why greedy works (exchange argument)**: Among the events available today, the one with the smallest end day is the most 'fragile' — it has the fewest days left. Any optimal schedule that attends a different available event today can be modified to attend the smallest-end-day one today and the other event later (still possible because the other has a later deadline) without losing any attended events. Repeating this swap proves earliest-deadline-first is optimal.

```javascript
