**Why greedy works (exchange argument)**: In any feasible group, swap the captain to the highest ratio inside; the total only depends on that ratio and the sum of qualities in the group. Replacing a member that's not the captain with someone of smaller quality (and ratio <= captain's) strictly lowers total. So the optimum chooses the k smallest qualities from the prefix sorted by ratio, for some choice of captain in the prefix. Iterating all captains finds the true minimum.

```javascript
